From 3efbd45f361540d6af9d08b06f0bf7d9c5930dd2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 11:34:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] make/autoconf: treat WSL build hosts as Linux

Buildroot can run inside WSL while cross-compiling OpenJDK for a Linux
target. Upstream OpenJDK classifies `*wsl*` as a Windows build host,
which then forces Windows path import/verification through fixpath.sh.

That path handling is only appropriate when actually building OpenJDK
for Windows. In this package we are building for Linux, and the WSL
classification causes configure to fail before the build starts.

Treat WSL as a Linux/Unix host in this context so configure uses normal
Unix path handling.

Signed-off-by: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
---
 make/autoconf/platform.m4 | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/make/autoconf/platform.m4 b/make/autoconf/platform.m4
index 37602bff454..a43e6dd4f26 100644
--- a/make/autoconf/platform.m4
+++ b/make/autoconf/platform.m4
@@ -196,8 +196,8 @@ AC_DEFUN([PLATFORM_EXTRACT_VARS_FROM_OS],
       VAR_OS=windows
       VAR_OS_ENV=windows.cygwin
       ;;
-    *wsl*)
-      VAR_OS=windows
-      VAR_OS_ENV=windows.wsl
+    *wsl*)
+      VAR_OS=linux
+      VAR_OS_TYPE=unix
       ;;
     *msys* | *mingw*)
       VAR_OS=windows
-- 
2.43.0
